<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-7E4AA1DB-2EBA-4D70-B1B4-5091B7E4B8FC" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-7E4AA1DB-2EBA-4D70-B1B4-5091B7E4B8FC" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">05 The process of the Measurement &amp; Control unit</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M057031-B22"><p class="- topic/p ">This is the functional description of the M&amp;C (Measurement &amp; Control) unit . 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The M&amp;C unit is used for : 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul " id="UL_D213A812CEA44F8E8754EFCFEC39C31F"><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_76A8AB7F96F94433B9499C07CA2A2558"><p class="- topic/p ">Detection of the leading-edge, width and position of the media . 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_E4DCFE27DD3944068BCD8BFB2A2C1B7E"><p class="- topic/p ">Automatic measurement of printed test-patterns to achieve an optimal print-quality. 
</p></li></ul></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="M057031-B23" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The M&amp;C Unit hardware</title><fig outputclass="figure" id="M057031-F24" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6E916C08-10F8-4F16-A8ED-603A3ABE1705-low.png" id="M057031-SH38" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6E916C08-10F8-4F16-A8ED-603A3ABE1705-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-0EC5CB74-809A-469A-96A1-07233061FEF8" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Physical specification and position</title><p class="- topic/p ">The M&amp;C unit is a full color scanner with a resolution of 400 DPI. The scanner is located at the left hand side of the printhead carriage. 
</p><fig id="M149179-F67" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-CF3290E2-8DA4-4E73-B3D3-802829503B0E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CF3290E2-8DA4-4E73-B3D3-802829503B0E-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The M&amp;C unit consists out of two parts : 
</p><ol id="OL_5524EBA1609C4114A999FBE30CAFA011" class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_B6929EADA3C74C4CA5701C088F35E0E0" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Measurement and control receiver PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 05PBA05 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">YMS_CAR_MC_SE</compsignal></comp> . 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This PBA receives the reflected light and converts the light into scan data. 
</p></li><li id="LI_2E46D59D741A4D0EB68F77CBA6CDD76D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Measurement and control LED PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 05PBA06 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">YMS_CAR_MC_SE</compsignal></comp> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This PBA contains LEDs to provide the necessary light for the scan process. 
</p></li></ol><p class="- topic/p ">The M&amp;C unit is installed on the left hand side of the printhead carriage. See : 
<xref keyref="05COMP01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-C84EECD3-BAF1-407D-AFF1-341C785F8FB5.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>05 The components of the Y Motion System</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The M&amp;C unit moves together with the printhead carriage. 
</p></section><section id="M057031-B26" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Functionality</title><p class="- topic/p ">The M&amp;C unit is used in the following situations 
</p><ol id="OL_389844F4B8274B75AB0F242D85DDA69D" class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_6481B1A9A42C471087252476D2AED985" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">New media handling :</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If a new media roll is inserted in the system 
</p><ol id="OL_5E4934D35A3A44189D1FD1499B451F12" class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_68ECDD5286D64EB09F61F993B090B1CF" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The media is fed into the printer until the M&amp;C unit detects the leading edge. 
</p></li><li id="LI_4A91DB5E8B744F17ACD15FB4DF0B182F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Feeding stops and M&amp;C unit detects the width and position of the media. 
</p></li><li id="LI_C2E1B6BB4F70423B87EC02E268D6BA98" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Now the media is fed back to the regular media stop position. 
</p></li></ol></li><li id="LI_1283719644EF4633AA1422B76B6BFBE8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Improve or correct print quality :</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">There are several tests to check the print quality. 
</p><ol id="OL_B0DC36A875884B4595E99FD236996BCE" class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_2A493624ABE9470EB094793E7BB053E1" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A test pattern is printed on the media. 
</p></li><li id="LI_084E0DFCAD2644B6B5CE8DAF9C6557DC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">This test pattern is measured and used to achieve an optimal print quality. 
</p></li></ol></li></ol></section><section id="M057031-B35" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The Data path</title><p class="- topic/p ">All data is sent to the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">µMORPF PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 21PBA02</compcodenr></comp> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">It passes through the following boards 
</p><ul id="UL_AA1FA57976924E848926C5F212711A0D" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_388DD64038814AE5A88DEEA4D75BB1D9" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Carriage PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 05PBA07 </compcodenr></comp> 
</p></li><li id="LI_DD3162DD8793474CA47D33D65A7F680B" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Embedded controller PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 21PBA03 </compcodenr></comp> 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">See diagram 
<xref keyref="05ELEC01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-C880D224-3EFC-4D9D-A7A7-CD4F6174FAE1.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>05 Electrical diagram Y motion system</xref>. 
</p></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-EDD196F8-AB74-4704-8B74-A25ED306422F.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
